                "href": "/profile/Darren-Walters-5"
            },
            "answer_text": "I\u2019m sorry to be kind of a jack-ass, but that\u2019s a fragment, not a question. But I know what you mean, and I think the idea is probably to hone rudimentary skills that are lost, frankly, because we keep letting the machines do it. I think there\u2019s nothing wrong with letting the calculator do the mundane stuff. But there\u2019s a huge difference between using the calculator, and you setting up the equations based on the information you\u2019re given. It\u2019s just like grammar: the reason there\u2019s no grammar-check on most word processors is because grammar can be somewhat subjective; the rules aren\u2019t hard and fast with English grammar, at any rate. You can spell check until your heart\u2019s content; what you can\u2019t check for is less concrete ideas, like form, content, flow, dangling modifiers, sentence structures, repetitions, main ideas and supporting ideas. Or, for that matter, superfluous ideas. ",
